  "text": "The results show that using features from LUV color space, gradient magnitude and quantized gradients, calculated from the average pixel values of rectangle regions, to train classifiers is a valid approach for detecting if parking spaces are occupied or not. The baseline classifiers suggested in de Almeida et al. [CITATION_1] perform marginally better when training and evaluation are done with images from the same camera, so for a parking lot surveillance application where training can be afforded to be redone for each camera, the classifiers presented here could perhaps be improved, either by including some features used in de Almeida et al. [CITATION_2] or by using a more dense grid when choosing rectangles for feature calculations, to better capture smaller details in the images.",
